reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on March 23, 2021
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars A new AT PS, and at 400W, perfect!
reviews.reviewText: My original PS was 200W. This is 400W, and it has a better mix of power connections. It really is new, not NOS. I'm quite impressed. Also, it's completely quiet. I couldn't hear it on my bench, and I had to put my hand to the fan to check if it was on. I will buy again IF there is EVER a need to do so again.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 26, 2020
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars If you have an old AT style computer, this will fix it
reviews.reviewText: We had a power supply die on an old AT style computer when we had a connection fail in cubes that should have been replaced 10 years ago. We needed the old computer to run a particular software package, so I bought this power supply and installed it. The computer is back up and running, and our special software package works great.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 7, 2021
reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars Can’t recommend this
reviews.reviewText: I’m really happy to see newly manufactured AT power supplies, with the hope of making retro systems easier and safer. At 400W, this provides plenty of power for vintage systems and has a good number of connectors. The power switch cable is a bit shorter than the power supply I replaced, and just barely fits in my mid-tower case. Overall on paper it looks great and I want to love it.However, I’ve gone through two of these power supplies and they are both providing too high of a voltage on both the 5V and 12V rails which will shorten the life of the system - and absolute no for retro system builds. With that in mind I cannot recommend this PSU and have editing my rating down accordingly.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 22, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 2.0 out of 5 stars Very light and cheap construction
reviews.reviewText: Poor execution for a power supply design that has been around since the near dawn of personal computers. This power supply is so light weight it feels like it’s empty. The power voltages on 12v and 5v are too high and out of spec. The power on cord with included switch is shorter than every other AT power supply I have ever owned. Over all this is a $12 power supply you would get direct from China, but for a $50 price tag. Disappointed more than anything, as it’s junk… why are companies building junk in 2022?

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 14, 2019
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Good for vintage gaming
reviews.reviewText: I got this for a vintage gaming PC (AMD K6) and wanted a brand new power supply for peace of mind instead of a used questionable one. It's exactly what you'd expect from an AT power supply, voltages within tolerance, quiet enough to not be a big deal, and it just works.
